                                    <p id="payment-methods">
                                      <strong>How can I pay? What are the available payment options?</strong>
                                      Our payments use Braintree as a gateway payment provider. Through this gateway we accept payments with most of the popular credit and debit cards
                                      (Visa, MasterCard, Maestro, American Express, Discover, JCB, Diner's Club, Carte Blanche, China UnionPay, Laser, Switch, Solo) and payments with PayPal.
                                      We also accept EMV (i.e. chip and pin) and 3D Secure cards for payments.
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      The Enhancv platform complies with latest PCI DSS rules and it is validated through Braintree's partner, Security Metrics.
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      An acceptable decline ratio for credit card payments is about 10%, but this may fluctuate so the recommended payment method by us is PayPal as it has a really good success rate.
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      You can access and see our available payment plans and current promotion offers here: <a href="https://app.enhancv.com/plans" target="_blank">Plans</a>.
                                      You have to be logged into the system to view this page.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="legacy-payments">
                                      <strong>I paid for a whole year a few months ago and now you have recurring payments. Am I required to pay again?</strong>
                                      â€‹Since March 2016 we enrolled our recurring monthly and yearly payments.
                                      For all the users that paid for a full year on the previous payment scheme we decided to give 3 months free access.
                                      If you are one of these users, after that period, you are going to be transferred to the Free plan
                                      and if you wish to continue using our pro features you will have to make a subscription with the new payment scheme we have enrolled.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="payment-model">
                                      <strong>Is this a one-time payment, or is it recurring?</strong>
                                      â€‹Our payments are recurring. We offer a monthly recurring subscription and an annual one which gives you 20% OFF from every monthly payment for the whole year.
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      You can cancel your subscription at any time and you won't be billed any more. You can later resubscribe at any moment you wish.
                                      If you want to use our paid services for one occasion only we suggest that you make a monthly subscription and cancel it afterwards so you will only get billed for one month.
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      We recommend that you follow our social profiles in <a href="https://www.facebook.com/enhancv/" target="_blank">Facebook</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/enhancv" target="_blank">Twitter</a>
                                      because we often publish promotional offers and discount promocodes for free access there.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="cancel-subscription">
                                      <strong>How can I cancel my subscription?</strong>
                                      You first must be logged into your account. You then have to follow this link: <a href="https://app.enhancv.com/settings/billing" target="_blank">Billing</a>.
                                      In this settings section you will find button labeled 'Suspend subscription'.
                                      Click it and confirm the unsubscribe. You will still have access to pro features for the paid period
                                      but afterwards you won't be billed again and you won't be able to download your resume without resubscribing if it contains pro features.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="apply-promocode">
                                      <strong>I have a valid promocode. How do I use it?</strong>
                                      You first have to navigate to the <a href="https://app.enhancv.com/plans" target="_blank">Plans</a> page.
                                      Before choosing a plan you have to apply the promocode by entering it's value in the promocode input below the plans boxes and clicking Apply.
                                      You should see the plan prices change accordingly afterwards. Now please choose the plan you want and continue by entering a valid payment method.
                                      You won't get charged the full price or you won't be charged at all for the promotional period depending on the promocode discount percentage.
                                      After the promocode period expires you will be charged the full price of the plan unless you have canceled your subscription beforehand!
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="payment-refund">
                                      <strong>How can I get a refund?</strong>
                                      To get a refund you should contact us and we will investigate the matter and explain the process.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="payment-invoice">
                                      <strong>I need an invoice for my payment. Where and when can I view or download it?</strong>
                                      Some time after a successful payment you will be sent an email containing an invoice pdf file for the payment attached in it.
                                      If you want to download it later you can also go to the  <a href="https://app.enhancv.com/settings/billing" target="_blank">Billing</a> page
                                      and scroll down to it's bottom and click on the download icon in the Receipt column of the Recent Payments History table.
                                      There can be a time period of a 1-2 hours right after the payment is executed when the payment invoice can be unavailable for download in the Billing section but it should be downloadable afterwards.
                                      Invoices won't be available for download for payments or promotions made before we enrolled our recurring payment model.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="billing-notification">
                                      <strong>Do I get notified before I get billed? When and how will I get a notice?</strong>
                                      Yes. You should receive an email 7 days before we are about to charge you every month unless you have canceled your subscription in that month.
                                      Please also check the Spam folder in your email clients as some messages can end up in it by mistake.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="payment-error">
                                      <strong>I am seeing a 'Processor declined' error message when I try to pay. What does this mean?</strong>
                                      â€‹This generic response indicates that your bank is unwilling to accept the transaction.
                                      The reasons vary. You will need to contact your bank for more details.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="card-rejected">
                                      <strong>For some reason my card keeps getting rejected? What can I do to pay?</strong>
                                      â€‹An acceptable decline ratio for credit card payments is about 10%, but this may fluctuate
                                      so this means that not all credit and debit card payments succeed and the reasons vary - the card may not be compatible or it may have expired,
                                      there may be insufficient funds in it or your bank may have declined the transaction.
                                      In these cases we recommend that you contact the bank that issued the card to get more information or just use a PayPal account for making the payment.
                                    </p>
