                                <div class="panel-body">
                                    <p id="pro-features">
                                      <strong>Which are the pro features that I'm using and how can I remove them?</strong>
                                      â€‹You can go to the <a href="https://app.enhancv.com/plans" target="_blank">Plans</a> page and click on the 'Remove Premium Features' button.
                                      It will open a popup with a list of the premium features used where you can confirm their removal.
                                      If you choose to remove them you can always undo the action immediately afterwards by clicking the Undo button to the left in the resume editor page.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="logo-removal">
                                      <strong>Can I remove your logo from the bottom of the resume pages?</strong>
                                      Yes. Just choose the Layout menu from the main toolbox to the left in the editor and after that click on the switch named Remove Logo.
                                      This is a pro feature and you will be required to pay to download your resume after using it!
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-rearrangement">
                                      <strong>Can I rearrange the sections and the items in them?</strong>
                                      Yes. You can drag the items in a section to reorder them by clicking and holding your left mouse button near the corners of the item box.
                                      You can use the left menu item 'Rearrange/Edit' to change the section positions or delete sections in the resume.
                                      You can also add different sections from the left toolbox menu when you click the '+New Sections' menu item.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="toggle-fields">
                                      <strong>How can I hide the date, location or link in a section item?</strong>
                                      Just click the section item you want to change and click on the last icon of a cogwheel from the upper small toolbox above it.
                                      From there you can show/hide different parts of the current section item including date, location and link.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-history">
                                      <strong>Can I revert an unwanted change I made to my resume and how?</strong>
                                      Yes, you can. We keep a history of the last actions you made.
                                      You can use it by clicking the Undo and Redo buttons which are located in the upper part of the main toolbox to the left in the editor.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-fontsize">
                                      <strong>Can I change the font size of the texts and headings in the resume?</strong>
                                      We currently do not offer the option to change the font size of the resume text and headings.
                                      You can try to change the font type to a more condensed one from the Fonts section in the left main toolbox. Most of the fonts are considered a paid feature mind you.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-resizing">
                                      <strong>Can I resize the different sections and items in them?</strong>
                                      For now we do not offer the possibility to resize the sections or their items and the margins between them.
                                      But we are considering making a condensed version of the resume and the possibility to switch from condensed to relaxed version in the near future. So stay tooned.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-templates">
                                      <strong>Do you have predefined templates with different styles?</strong>
                                      No. For now we do not offer different resume templates for different professions. It is something that will be implemented in the near future.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="multiple-resumes">
                                      <strong>Can I have multiple resumes in one account?</strong>
                                      Sorry for now you have to create a new profile for a new resume.
                                      But we are currently working on multiple resumes per account and resume duplication with a single click.
                                      This is one of the main reasons why we decided to change our payments to a subscription model.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-export">
                                      <strong>Can I export my resume as a MS Word document or HTML code?</strong>
                                      No. We provide only export to pdf files for now because it is the expected standard for resumes at this point.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-missing-info">
                                      <strong>Why is my resume info cut down after choosing the Free plan to download it?</strong>
                                      This happened because you have used paid features in your resume and you have chosen the Free plan.
                                      You must have no pro features in order to download your pdf.
                                      This is why you are offered to remove all the paid features in a popup window that opens after you click on the 'Remove Premium Features' button on the Plans page.
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      After you confirm the remove we strip all paid features for you.
                                      One of the rules for using the Free plan is that you can't have more that 15 section items for the whole resume.
                                      For example one language in the Language section and one passion entry in the Passions section are considered to be two section items.
                                      So we strip the last 15 section items added.
                                      That's why your resume info gets stripped after removing pro features.
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      You can undo the removal action by clicking on the Undo button in the upper part of the main left toolbar,
                                      but only if you haven't made a lot of other changes afterwards because we only keep a limited history of the last changes made to the resume.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="resume-single-date">
                                      <strong>How do I leave a single date and not a date period in a resume section item?</strong>
                                      Yes, you are able to do that. You just have to leave the 'to' period dropdown controls empty and select values only for the 'from' controls in the date-picker popover toolbox.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="certificate-images">
                                      <strong>How can I upload an image for each of my certificates?</strong>
                                      If you try to use the certificates section you won't be able to do this for now.
                                      But if you use the books section and rename it's heading to Certificates, then you'll have the possibility to upload images to every entry.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="gpa-images">
                                      <strong>What does GPA stand for?</strong>
                                      GPA means grade point average. This is the average grade score received for the whole period of study in one educational facility.
                                    </p>
                                    <p id="other-problem">
                                      <strong>I am experiencing problems with my resume and none of the above questions refers to them. What do I do?</strong>
                                      Please try to refresh the page a couple of times. You can press the Ctrl+R key combination a couple of times.
                                      This way you will make sure you are using the latest version of our platform and not cached old copy of the editor.
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      If this doesn't help and you are still having trouble working with the editor,
                                      you can get in touch with our support team by using the Intercom help chat in the editor if you have a profile with us
                                      or by writing us an email explaining the difficulties you are having.
                                    </p>
